Software Requirements Specification (SRS)
Project: AI Mental Health Support Application
1. Overview
AI-powered mobile app that provides mental health support through a conversational chatbot. System uses multi-modal inputs (text, voice, optional image, screen usage behavior) to detect user emotions and generate adaptive responses.
2. Objectives
- Provide real-time emotional support via chatbot
- Detect user emotional state with high sensitivity (~80%)
- Combine behavioral and conversational data for better accuracy
3. Scope
- Mobile application (Android/iOS)
- Chat-based interaction (primary feature)
- Optional voice and image input
- Screen usage tracking (with user consent)
- Emotion detection + adaptive response system
4. Functional Requirements
4.1 User Interaction
- User can send text messages
- User can use voice input (optional)
- User can upload image (optional, not required)

4.2 Chatbot System
- Respond in therapist-like tone (empathetic, calm)
- Maintain conversation context (session memory)
- Generate dynamic responses based on emotional state

4.3 Emotion Detection
- Analyze: text, voice, image (optional), screen usage
- Output: single emotional state score/label

4.4 Screen Usage Tracking
- Collect: screen time, app usage frequency, active hours
- Use as contextual input

4.5 Emotion Fusion Engine
- Combine inputs into unified emotional state

4.6 Dashboard
- Display emotional trends and usage patterns

4.7 Settings
- Enable/disable features and privacy controls
5. Non-Functional Requirements
- Performance: real-time response (<2 seconds)
- Usability: simple UI, chat-focused
- Security: user consent, secure storage
- Scalability: modular architecture
6. System Architecture
- Frontend: Flutter / React Native
- Backend: FastAPI / Node.js
- NLP: Transformers
- Modules: chat, emotion detection, behavior tracking
7. Assumptions
- Works with text only
- Image optional
- Tracking requires consent
8. Constraints
- No required facial data
- Privacy compliance
- No clinical diagnosis
9. Deliverables
- Mobile app
- Backend API
- Emotion detection system
- Dashboard